#: ../../effects_and_compositions/video_effects/color_image_correction/color_temperature.rst:28
msgid ""
"**Temperature** - Set the temperature in :term:`Kelvin<kelvin>`. Allowed "
"values are from 1,000 to 40,000, default is 6,500K."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/video_effects/color_image_correction/color_temperature.rst:30
msgid ""
"**Mix** - Set the mix with filtered output. Allowed values are from 0.0 to "
"1.0, default value is 1.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/video_effects/color_image_correction/color_temperature.rst:32
msgid ""
"**Saturation** - Set the color :term:`saturation`. Allowed values are from 0 "
"to 1, default value is 0.5."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/video_effects/color_image_correction/color_temperature.rst:34
msgid ""
"**Preserve lightness** - Set the amount of preserving :term:`lightness`. "
"Allowed values are from 0 to 1, default value is 0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../effects_and_compositions/video_effects/color_image_correction/color_temperature.rst:38
msgid ""
"Color temperature is measured in degrees Kelvin. Lower values correct for "
"\"warmer\" lighting, higher values correct for \"cool\" lighting. the "
"default value of +6,500K is unity."
msgstr ""
